This category of Mitigations emphasizes the importance of improving and enhancing ventilation systems in buildings. It includes measures such as increasing ventilation rates, using air filters and purifiers, and incorporating natural lighting and ventilation in building design. The list also mentions the need for proper maintenance and cleaning of ventilation systems, as well as the use of advanced ventilation technologies such as UV germicidal irradiation. Additionally, the category highlights the significance of respiratory hygiene practices, such as wearing masks and practicing good respiratory hygiene, along with maintaining physical distance. Overall, the Mitigations in this category focus on creating and maintaining a well-ventilated and healthy indoor environment to reduce the spread of contagious diseases.